# AI Work Progress - Sweet.TV Kodi Addon

Project context, conventions, and gotchas live in [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md).
Architecture, API, debugging, localization deep-dives are in [docs/](docs/).
This file tracks **what's done and what's left**, nothing else.

## Phases

### Phase 1: Core Live TV + EPG [DONE]
- [x] Analyze Enigma2 reference plugin for API understanding
- [x] Repo structure (README, configs, addon skeleton)
- [x] sweet.tv API client (auth, channels, EPG, streams)
- [x] IPTV Manager integration (channels + EPG via socket)
- [x] URL router and main menu
- [x] Settings UI (bitrate, adult filter, pairing)
- [x] Device pairing flow with on-screen dialogs
- [x] Auto-launch pairing on first use
- [x] Live stream playback (Kodi built-in HLS player)
- [x] Live TV channel browsing with sweet.tv categories
- [x] Channels appear in Kodi's native TV section via IPTV Manager
- [x] PVR channel groups from sweet.tv categories + Pinned Channels (localized)
- [x] Bitrate cap setting
- [x] One-click PVR Simple Client configuration from addon settings

### Phase 2: Archive/Catchup [DONE]
- [x] Browse channels with archive support via addon UI
- [x] Archive browsing organized by sweet.tv categories + Pinned Channels
- [x] Browse archive by day (with localized day names)
- [x] Play archived programs through addon UI
- [x] PVR catchup playback from TV guide (catchup-id in XMLTV EPG)

### Phase 3: Parental Lock [DONE]
- [x] Adult channel filtering (show/hide via setting)
- [x] Optional addon-level PIN gate for adult content (asked once per Kodi session)
- Note: not integrated with Kodi's built-in master lock — that's profile-switching only and not addon-accessible by design

### Phase 4: Subscription Info [DONE]
- [x] Subscription Information dialog with parsed data
- [x] Account status, plan, active services
- [x] Days remaining on each service
- [x] Balance, parental control state

